document_api_meta.title: Get Order Detail
document_api_meta.env_desc: Get the detailed order information of an order, including important attributes such as order status, shipping addresses, payment details, price and tax info, and package information.

request_header_param.name: x-tts-access-token
request_header_param.desc: The seller access_token value from [Get Access Token](https://partner.tiktokshop.com/docv2/page/678e3a3292b0f40314a92d75#Get%20Access%20Token%20API), when user_type = 0. Follow this [guide](https://partner.tiktokshop.com/docv2/page/678e3a344ddec3030b238fa0) to get seller access_token.

request_query_param.name: app_key
request_query_param.desc: Every single app will have a unique key. Please use the specific key assigned to your app.

request_query_param.name: sign
request_query_param.desc: Signature generated by gen algorithm. When you send API requests to TTS, you must sign them so that TTS can identify the senders.

request_query_param.name: timestamp
request_query_param.desc: Unix timestamp GMT (UTC+00:00). This timestamp is used across all API requests. Developers can use this convert to local time.

request_query_param.name: ids
request_query_param.desc:
A list of TikTok Shop order ID values.
Max count: 50

request_query_param.name: shop_cipher
request_query_param.desc:
Use this property to pass shop information in requesting the API. Failure in passing the correct value when requesting the API for cross-border shops will return incorrect response. 
Get by API [Get Authorization Shop](https://partner.tiktokshop.com/docv2/page/6507ead7b99d5302be949ba9?external_id=6507ead7b99d5302be949ba9)

response_param.name: code
response_param.desc: The success or failure status code returned in API response.

response_param.name: message
response_param.desc: The success or failure messages returned in API response. Reasons of failure will be described in the message.

response_param.name: request_id
response_param.desc: Request log

response_param.name: data
response_param.desc: Specific return information

response_param.name: ^orders
response_param.desc: Order information.

response_param.name: ^^id
response_param.desc: A unique identifier for a TikTok Shop order.

response_param.name: ^^cancellation_initiator
response_param.desc:
The initiator of a cancellation request.
Possible values: 
- `SELLER`
- `BUYER`
- `SYSTEM`

response_param.name: ^^shipping_provider
response_param.desc: The name of the current shipping provider.

response_param.name: ^^shipping_provider_id
response_param.desc: The ID of the current shipping provider.

response_param.name: ^^user_id
response_param.desc: The buyer's user ID.

response_param.name: ^^status
response_param.desc:
The order status.
Possible values:
- `UNPAID`: The order is placed, but payment is not yet completed.
- `ON_HOLD`: The order is accepted and is waiting for fulfillment so the buyer may still cancel without the seller’s approval. If `order_type=PRE_ORDER`, it also means the product is still awaiting release so payment will only be authorized 1 day before the release, but the seller should start preparing for the release.
- `AWAITING_SHIPMENT`: The order is ready for shipment, but no items are shipped yet.
- `PARTIALLY_SHIPPING`: Some items in the order are shipped, but not all.
- `AWAITING_COLLECTION`: The shipment is arranged, but the package is waiting to be collected by the carrier.
- `IN_TRANSIT`: The package is collected by the carrier and delivery is in progress.
- `DELIVERED`: The package is delivered to buyer.
- `COMPLETED`: The order is completed, and no further returns or refunds are allowed.
- `CANCELLED`: The order is cancelled.

response_param.name: ^^rts_time
response_param.desc:
The time seller shipped the order (call Ship Order endpoint successfully).
Unix timestamp.

response_param.name: ^^payment
response_param.desc: Payment info about a TikTok Shop order.

response_param.name: ^^^currency
response_param.desc: Currency for payment.

response_param.name: ^^^sub_total
response_param.desc:
Buyer paid subtotal of all the SKUs in the order. For the US market, this is pre-tax total amount.
`sub_total` = `original_total_product_price` - `seller_discount` - `platform_discount`

response_param.name: ^^^shipping_fee
response_param.desc:
Buyer paid shipping fee. 
`shipping_fee` = `original_shipping_fee` - `shipping_fee_seller_discount` - `shipping_fee_platform_discount`
For the US market, this is pre-tax total amount.

response_param.name: ^^^seller_discount
response_param.desc: Product discount by seller.

response_param.name: ^^^platform_discount
response_param.desc: Product discount by platform.

response_param.name: ^^^total_amount
response_param.desc:
Buyer paid total amount.
`total_amount` = `sub_total` + `shipping_fee` + `taxes` + `retail_delivery_fee`

response_param.name: ^^^original_total_product_price
response_param.desc:
Total original price of products (VAT included for crossborder shop).
For the US market, this is pre-tax total amount.

response_param.name: ^^^original_shipping_fee
response_param.desc: Shipping fee before discount

response_param.name: ^^^shipping_fee_seller_discount
response_param.desc: Shipping fee discount provided by seller for an order that will not qualify for co-funded reimbursement. **Note**: If an order meets the minimum order value for co-funded reimbursement, this will be 0. In this case, refer to `shipping_fee_cofunded_discount` for the shipping discount the buyer received.

response_param.name: ^^^shipping_fee_platform_discount
response_param.desc: Shipping fee discount by platform.

response_param.name: ^^^shipping_fee_cofunded_discount
response_param.desc: Shipping fee discount provided by seller, eligible for co-funded reimbursement upon order delivery, based on Co-Funded Free Shipping program terms. **Note**: This will be 0 for orders that did not meet minimum order value for co-funded reimbursement. In this case, refer to `shipping_fee_seller_discount` for the shipping discount the buyer received.

response_param.name: ^^^tax
response_param.desc: Buyer paid total taxes of the order. Applicable to crossborder shops and the US market.

response_param.name: ^^^small_order_fee
response_param.desc:
Small order fee for TH.
Small order fee is for Thailand only. small order fee means that the platform will set a minimum order spending amount, when the order amount is lower than the minimum order spending amount, the user needs to pay small order fee to meet the platform minimum spending amount. 
e.g. Minimum order spending amount is 100, order amount is 80. So the small order fee will be 20.

response_param.name: ^^^shipping_fee_tax
response_param.desc: The tax on the shipping price.

response_param.name: ^^^product_tax
response_param.desc: The tax on the total item price.

response_param.name: ^^^retail_delivery_fee
response_param.desc: RDF (retail delivery fee). Available only in the US market.

response_param.name: ^^^buyer_service_fee
response_param.desc: A service fee is charged on every transaction made. The charge is applied from the fifth order onwards and collected directly from customers during checkout. Only available in Indonesia market.

response_param.name: ^^^handling_fee
response_param.desc: A fee charged to buyers to cover the additional processing, handling, and/or installment costs associated with the chosen payment method.

response_param.name: ^^^shipping_insurance_fee
response_param.desc:
The cost incurred by the buyers for coverage against loss or damage to goods during transit.
**Note**: Available only in the Indonesia market.

response_param.name: ^^^item_insurance_fee
response_param.desc:
The cost incurred by the buyers for coverage against defects or damage to the product after purchase.
**Note**: Only available in the US and Indonesia markets.

response_param.name: ^^^item_insurance_tax
response_param.desc:
The tax paid on the insurance purchased by buyers.

Note: Only applicable in US market.

response_param.name: ^^recipient_address
response_param.desc: `recipient_address` is not available under `UNPAID` and `ON_HOLD` status.

response_param.name: ^^^full_address
response_param.desc: The complete recipient addresses information.

response_param.name: ^^^phone_number
response_param.desc: The telephone number of the buyer. Please notice, if this order uses platform logistics, phone number will be desensitized.

response_param.name: ^^^name

response_param.name: ^^^first_name
response_param.desc: The first name of the recipient. If the buyer does not provide their first and last name separately, this parameter will have the same value as the "name" parameter.

response_param.name: ^^^last_name
response_param.desc: The last name of the recipient. If the buyer does not provide their first and last name separately, this parameter will be empty.

response_param.name: ^^^first_name_local_script
response_param.desc:
Recipient first name in katakana.
**Note**: Applicable only for the JP market.

response_param.name: ^^^last_name_local_script
response_param.desc:
Recipient last name in katakana.
**Note**: Applicable only for the JP market.

response_param.name: ^^^region_code
response_param.desc: Region code.

response_param.name: ^^^postal_code
response_param.desc: The postal code that can be used by seller for shipping (in the U.S, this is the ZIP code).

response_param.name: ^^^post_town
response_param.desc:
Post town of the address
Note: Available only in UK market

response_param.name: ^^^address_line1
response_param.desc: The first line of the street address.

response_param.name: ^^^address_line2
response_param.desc: The second line of the street address

response_param.name: ^^^address_line3
response_param.desc:
The third line of the street address. 
Applicable only for the BR market.

response_param.name: ^^^address_line4
response_param.desc:
The fourth line of the street address.
Applicable only for the BR market.

response_param.name: ^^^district_info
response_param.desc: District information list.

response_param.name: ^^^^address_level_name
response_param.desc: The name of administrative division that can be used by seller for ship. e.g. state/county/city/district/town etc.

response_param.name: ^^^^address_name
response_param.desc: Administrative area name. eg: London

response_param.name: ^^^^address_level
response_param.desc: Administrative district level code. Value can be L0/L1/L2/L3/L4. eg. US is L0

response_param.name: ^^^delivery_preferences
response_param.desc: Contains all of the delivery instructions provided by the buyer for the shipping address. Currently, only available in the US market.

response_param.name: ^^^^drop_off_location
response_param.desc: Drop-off location selected by the buyer.

response_param.name: ^^^address_detail
response_param.desc: Full buyer detail address.

response_param.name: ^^buyer_message
response_param.desc: The note from buyer.

response_param.name: ^^create_time
response_param.desc: The date and time that the order was created. Unix timestamp.

response_param.name: ^^tracking_number
response_param.desc: Tracking number. Available after ship package.

response_param.name: ^^cancel_reason
response_param.desc: The reason for cancelling. [See here](https://partner.tiktokshop.com/docv2/page/650b28280fcef602bf435096#Back%20To%20Top) for more information.

response_param.name: ^^rts_sla_time
response_param.desc: The latest shipping time specified by the platform. Unix timestamp.

response_param.name: ^^paid_time
response_param.desc: The date and time that the order was paid. Unix timestamp.

response_param.name: ^^fulfillment_type
response_param.desc:
Fulfillment type. 
Only orders with fulfillment type can be shipped by sellers.
Possible values:
- `FULFILLMENT_BY_SELLER`: a method where sellers fulfill orders directly from their own inventory, without using TikTok's fulfillment centers. In this model, the seller is responsible for storing, packaging, and shipping the product to customers.
- `FULFILLMENT_BY_TIKTOK`: a service offered by TikTok that enables sellers to send their products to TikTok's fulfillment centers. TikTok then takes care of storing, picking, packing, and shipping the products to customers.
- `FULFILLMENT_BY_DILAYANI_TOKOPEDIA`: a method where Tokopedia GoTo Logistics provides warehousing and logistics services to sellers and charges a fee for the service.

response_param.name: ^^seller_note
response_param.desc: This field return the note, which seller notes in TikTok Seller Center.

response_param.name: ^^tts_sla_time
response_param.desc:
The latest collection time specified by the platform.
Unix timestamp.

response_param.name: ^^cancel_order_sla_time
response_param.desc:
The automatic cancellation time for orders specified by the platform.
Unix timestamp.

response_param.name: ^^update_time
response_param.desc:
Time of order status changes.
Unix timestamp.

response_param.name: ^^packages
response_param.desc: List of packages included in this order

response_param.name: ^^^id

response_param.name: ^^delivery_type

Indicates whether it is a PickUp DropOff (PUDO) location. The PUDO location is selected by the buyer when placing orders. 
- `HOME_DELIVERY`: not a PUDO location

response_param.name: ^^is_sample_order
response_param.desc: Use this field to determine whether the order is a sample order.

Indicate whether the order is combined or split.

response_param.name: ^^delivery_option_id

response_param.desc: Order should arrive by this date to be considered on-time and to avoid late delivery penalties.

response_param.name: ^^payment_method_name
response_param.desc: Payment method name, only for display

response_param.name: ^^payment_card_type

response_param.name: ^^channel_entity_national_registry_id

response_param.name: ^^payment_method_code

For card transactions (credit/debit card), this field will be transaction authorization code. For PIX transactions, this field will be E2E ID.

response_param.name: ^^shipping_due_time

response_param.name: ^^line_items

response_param.name: ^^^sku_id

response_param.name: ^^^product_name

response_param.name: ^^^sku_name

response_param.name: ^^^sku_image

response_param.name: ^^^original_price

response_param.name: ^^^sale_price

response_param.name: ^^^pfand_fee
response_param.desc:
Deposit fee that is applied to certain products, typically beverage containers such as bottles or cans.
**Note** Only available in Germany market

response_param.name: ^^^platform_discount
response_param.desc: Platform discount amount, please refer to the currency of `payment_info`.

response_param.name: ^^^display_status
response_param.desc:
- `UNPAID`: The order is placed, but payment is not yet completed.
- `AWAITING_SHIPMENT`: The order is ready for shipment, but no items are shipped yet.
- `AWAITING_COLLECTION`:  The shipment is arranged, but the package is waiting to be collected by the carrier.
- `IN_TRANSIT`: The package is collected by the carrier and delivery is in progress.
- `DELIVERED`: The package is delivered to buyer.
- `COMPLETED`: The order is completed, and no further returns or refunds are allowed.
- `CANCELLED`: The order is canceled.

response_param.name: ^^^cancel_user
response_param.desc:
The initiator of a cancellation request:
- `BUYER`
- `SELLER`
- `OPERATOR`
- `SYSTEM`

response_param.name: ^^^sku_type
response_param.desc:
[**Deprecated**: This field is deprecated and will be removed in a future API version. Use `order_type` instead.]
The order line type:
Possible values based on region:
**All regions**
- `NORMAL`: An item that is in stock and available for immediate purchase and fulfillment.
- `ZERO_LOTTERY:` An item purchased during a lottery event in TikTok LIVE.
- `SHOP_PARTNER`: An item purchased from a TikTok Shop partner store.
**US**
- `PRE_ORDER`: An item that is not yet available or released. Fulfillment starts on a specific date in the future.
- `MADE_TO_ORDER`: An item that is produced only after the order is received. Fulfillment starts after the product is produced.

response_param.name: ^^^seller_sku
response_param.desc: The seller stock keeping unit (SKU) of the item.

response_param.name: ^^^shipping_provider_id
response_param.desc: The shipping provider ID of the item.

response_param.name: ^^^seller_discount
response_param.desc: Seller discount amount. Please refer to the currency of `payment_info`.

response_param.name: ^^^currency
response_param.desc: Currency for payment.

response_param.name: ^^^package_id
response_param.desc: An order can contain one or more packages based on how the seller chooses to ship. Each package has a unique `package_id` (and also a `tracking_id`, which is used to track the progress of the package as it is shipped). For local sellers in the US and UK markets, the `package_id` and `package_status` property will not be returned before the package is shipped

response_param.name: ^^^rts_time
response_param.desc:
The time seller shipped line order (call Ship Order endpoint successfully).
Unix timestamp.

response_param.name: ^^^item_tax
response_param.desc: Item tax detail.

response_param.name: ^^^^tax_type
response_param.desc:
Tax type.
- `SALES_TAX` (US market sales tax)
Currently only sales tax is available.

response_param.name: ^^^^tax_amount
response_param.desc: Tax amount.

response_param.name: ^^^^tax_rate
response_param.desc: Tax rate.

response_param.name: ^^^package_status
response_param.desc:
The package status of the item:
- `TO_FULFILL`: package waiting seller to arrange shipment.
- `PROCESSING`: package shipment has been arranged by seller. Waiting carrier to collect the parcel.
- `FULFILLING`: package has been collected by carrier and in transit.
- `COMPLETED`: package has been delivered.
- `CANCELLED`: package has been canceled. Normally, the package is canceled due to the package being lost or damaged.

response_param.name: ^^^shipping_provider_name
response_param.desc: The shipping provider name of the item.

response_param.name: ^^^is_gift
response_param.desc: Indicates whether the current order line is a gift.

response_param.name: ^^^cancel_reason
response_param.desc: Item cancellation reason.

response_param.name: ^^^small_order_fee
response_param.desc: Small order fee for TH.

response_param.name: ^^^retail_delivery_fee
response_param.desc: RDF (retail delivery fee). Available only in the US market.

response_param.name: ^^^tracking_number
response_param.desc: Tracking number. Available after package has been shipped.

response_param.name: ^^^buyer_service_fee
response_param.desc: A service fee is charged on every transaction made. The charge is applied from the fifth order onwards and collected directly from customers during checkout. Only available in Indonesia market.

response_param.name: ^^^handling_duration_days
response_param.desc:
[**Deprecated**: This field is deprecated and will be removed in a future API version. Use `handling_duration` instead.]
The number of business days required for the seller to process the order and hand it over to a shipping carrier after the order is placed. 
Applicable only if the value for `sku_type` is `MADE_TO_ORDER`.

response_param.name: ^^^is_dangerous_good
response_param.desc: Whether the SKU is a hazmat item. When creating the label for a hazmat item, you must follow the platform rules to put certain items into one package. Please refer to the relationship between `sku_id` and `package_id` to determine how to follow platform rules.

response_param.name: ^^^needs_prescription
response_param.desc: A flag to indicate whether the included product requires a prescription.

response_param.name: ^^^gift_retail_price
response_param.desc:
Retail price of the free item in orders Live giveaway, free sample and gift with purchase. For other orders, this field always returns 0.
This amount can be used for free samples and live giveaway order invoice in Brazil

response_param.name: ^^shipping_type
response_param.desc:
The method of delivery.
- `TIKTOK`: shipping service provided by TikTok. The seller should obtain shipping label from TikTok.
- `SELLER`: seller provides shipping, including through 3rd party fulfillment providers on behalf of the seller.

response_param.name: ^^buyer_email
response_param.desc: The anonymized email address of the buyer. It is not recommended to send messages directly to this email address. If you need to contact the buyer, please go to Seller Center - Buyer Messages page.

response_param.name: ^^delivery_time
response_param.desc: The timestamp of the order's status update to `DELIVERED`.

response_param.name: ^^need_upload_invoice
response_param.desc:
Whether an invoice needs to be uploaded (only for Brazil market).
- `UNKNOWN`
- `NEED_INVOICE`
- `NO_NEED`
- `INVOICE_UPLOADED`

response_param.name: ^^is_cod
response_param.desc: This option is for sellers that accept cash payment on delivery which is rare. Buyers will pay in cash upon receipt of package. Default value is `FALSE`. Only applicable to countries where Cash on Delivery (COD) is supported.

response_param.name: ^^request_cancel_time
response_param.desc: Buyer request cancel time.

response_param.name: ^^delivery_option_required_delivery_time
response_param.desc: Order should be delivered before this time.

response_param.name: ^^delivery_option_name
response_param.desc: Delivery option name. For display purposes only.

response_param.name: ^^is_buyer_request_cancel
response_param.desc: True when the buyer has a pending cancellation request

response_param.name: ^^delivery_due_time
response_param.desc: If the order hasn't updated its status to `DELIVERED` before this time, the order will be automatically canceled by TikTok Shop.

response_param.name: ^^collection_time
response_param.desc: The timestamp of the order's status update to `IN_TRANSIT`.

response_param.name: ^^is_on_hold_order
response_param.desc: Indicates whether the order experienced or will be experienced `ON_HOLD` status.

response_param.name: ^^cancel_time
response_param.desc: The timestamp of the order's status update to `CANCELLED`.

response_param.name: ^^is_replacement_order
response_param.desc: When true, this is a replacement order.

response_param.name: ^^replaced_order_id
response_param.desc: The order ID for the order that is being replaced. Returned only if `is_replacement_order` = `true`

response_param.name: ^^collection_due_time
response_param.desc: If the order hasn't updated its status to `IN_TRANSIT` before this time, the order will be automatically canceled by TikTok Shop

response_param.name: ^^pick_up_cut_off_time
response_param.desc: To avoid LDR, you must ensure the package is picked up by this time. Only applicable in Southeast Asia regions.

response_param.name: ^^fast_dispatch_sla_time
response_param.desc:
The latest collection time to gain incentives of NDD (Next Day Delivery) project. Unix timestamp
Only available in Thailand and Philippines.

response_param.name: ^^commerce_platform
response_param.desc:
The platform where the order was placed.
Possible values:
- TIKTOK_SHOP
- TOKOPEDIA
**Note**: Available only in the Indonesia market.

response_param.name: ^^order_type
response_param.desc:
The order type.
Possible values based on region:
**All regions**
- `NORMAL`: An item that is in stock and available for immediate purchase and fulfillment.
- `ZERO_LOTTERY`: An order placed during a lottery event in TikTok LIVE.
**US**
- `PRE_ORDER`: An advance order for items that are not yet available or released. Fulfillment starts on a specific date in the future.
- `MADE_TO_ORDER`: An order for items that are produced only after the order is received. Fulfillment starts after the product is produced.
- `BACK_ORDER`: An order for items that are out of stock but expected to be restocked. Fulfillment starts after the product is restocked.
Returns an empty value for standard orders or other types that don't fall into the above categories.

response_param.name: ^^release_date
response_param.desc:
The date on which order handling starts and the status of the order changes to [`AWAITING_SHIPMENT`](https://partner.tiktokshop.com/docv2/page/650b1b4bbace3e02b76d1011).
Applicable only if the `order_type` is `PRE_ORDER`.

response_param.name: ^^handling_duration
response_param.desc:
The duration for the seller to process the order and hand it over to a shipping carrier after the order is placed. 
Applicable only if the `order_type` is `MADE_TO_ORDER` or `BACK_ORDER`.

response_param.name: ^^^days
response_param.desc: The number of days.

response_param.name: ^^^type
response_param.desc:
Indicates if the duration is calculated in calendar days or business days.
Possible values:
- `CALENDAR_DAY`: Represents consecutive days, including weekends and holidays.
- `BUSINESS_DAY`: Represents business days, excluding weekends and public holidays.
Default: `BUSINESS_DAY`

response_param.name: ^^auto_combine_group_id
response_param.desc: An identifier assigned to orders from the same customer during a LIVE session to facilitate combined order shipping when "auto-combination" is activated in Seller Center.

response_param.name: ^^cpf_name
response_param.desc: Name belonging to the CPF number for the Brazil market.

response_param.name: ^^is_exchange_order
response_param.desc:
When TRUE, this is an exchange order.
Note: Only available in US and UK.

response_param.name: ^^exchange_source_order_id
response_param.desc:
If the order is an exchange order, this field returns the original order's order ID, from which the exchange order was generated. 
Returned only if is_exchange_order = true.
Note: Only available in US and UK.

response_param.name: ^^consultation_id
response_param.desc:
An ID to identify the corresponding ePharmacy consultation. 
Applicable only if an ePharmacy consultation was initiated. Not applicable if the prescription was provided by the customer through an image upload.

response_param.name: ^^fast_delivery_program
response_param.desc:
A badge presented on the merchandise to tell the buyer that the seller participates in the fast delivery program, such that the order should arrive in a promised time period.
Possible values:
- `3_DAY_DELIVERY`
Not returned if order did not meet fast delivery
program requirements.
Note: Applicable only for the US market.
